co-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104neh1665702734617.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/neh1665702734617.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/neh1665702734617.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"neh1665702734617\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      delay textptr check\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Disable textpointer check during Fetch requests.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"neh1665702734617__topic_d59414e1_d59415e1_d59416e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59417e1_d59418e1_d59419e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$SYB_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">= delay textptr check</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"neh1665702734617__section_xgz_4nw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1217390e63\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59423e1_d59424e1_d59425e1\">This option is required for single table views which\n            contain both a segmented field (Text or Image) and a field whose name is renamed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59426e1_d59427e1_d59428e1\">When this option is set on, the textpointer check is\n            not performed during the Fetch request so that the Fetch can be performed over the view\n            with the renamed fields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59429e1_d59430e1_d59431e1\">Please note that:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"neh1665702734617__ul_mwd_pnw_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"neh1665702734617__li_d26651e1_d26652e1_d26653e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59432e1_d59433e1_d59434e1\">Segmented fields can never be renamed.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"neh1665702734617__li_d26654e1_d26655e1_d26656e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59435e1_d59436e1_d59437e1\">Primary key fields cannot be renamed in views\n                  which contain segmented fields.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"neh1665702734617__p_d59438e1_d59439e1_d59440e1\">Multi-table views do not require this option since the\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">delay textptr check</code> method is always used for multi-table views.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530225\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530225\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "delay textptr check Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 delay textptr check Disable textpointer check during Fetch requests. USYS$SYB_PARAMS = delay textptr check Description This option is required for single table views which contain both a segmented field (Text or Image) and a field whose name is renamed. When this option is set on, the textpointer check is not performed during the Fetch request so that the Fetch can be performed over the view with the renamed fields. Please note that: Segmented fields can never be renamed. Primary key fields cannot be renamed in views which contain segmented fields. Multi-table views do not require this option since the delay textptr check method is always used for multi-table views. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}